---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageShell from '../../components/system/PageShell.astro';
import Badge from '../../components/system/Badge.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <PageShell class="experience-shell">
    <header class="page-header"><Badge tone="accent">Experience</Badge><h1>Different systems. The same question: where does trust live?</h1><p class="intro">My experience has moved between building, defending, assessing, and teaching. That range is useful because finance systems, security systems, and ordinary software all fail in surprisingly human ways.</p></header>
    <div class="timeline">
      <article class="timeline-row"><div class="date">2024 — now</div><div><h2>Exploit Forge / Offensive Security Engineer</h2><p>I work across authorized security assessments, vulnerability research, custom tooling, and automation. The job is part investigation, part engineering, and part making a complicated failure understandable to the people who need to fix it.</p><div class="tags"><span>Red team</span><span>Research</span><span>Automation</span></div></div></article>
      <article class="timeline-row"><div class="date">2023</div><div><h2>Platview Nigeria / Cybersecurity Analyst</h2><p>Defensive work gave me the other side of the conversation: monitoring, incident response, threat intelligence, and the patience required to distinguish a real signal from a noisy environment.</p><div class="tags"><span>Monitoring</span><span>Incident response</span><span>Defense</span></div></div></article>
      <article class="timeline-row"><div class="date">2021 — now</div><div><h2>Independent practice</h2><p>Alongside client and research work, I build personal systems, publish technical notes, and mentor engineers. The repositories are part of that practice: a way to turn ideas into something that can be inspected, used, and challenged.</p><div class="tags"><span>Engineering</span><span>Consulting</span><span>Mentorship</span></div></div></article>
    </div>
  </PageShell>
</Layout>

<style>
  .experience-shell { max-width: 980px; }
  .page-header { max-width: 780px; padding: 1.5rem 0 3rem; }
  h1 { margin-top: 1rem; color: var(--text); font-size: clamp(2.3rem, 10vw, 5rem); line-height: 1; letter-spacing: 0; }
  .intro, .timeline-row p { margin-top: 1rem; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.96rem; font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.8; }
  .timeline { border-top: 1px solid var(--border-muted); }
  .timeline-row { display: grid; gap: 0.7rem; padding: 1.25rem 0 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-muted); }
  .date { color: var(--accent); font: 0.6rem 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  h2 { color: var(--text); font-size: 1.2rem; line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: 0; }
  .tags { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.45rem; margin-top: 1rem; }
  .tags span { padding: 0.35rem 0.55rem; border: 1px solid var(--border-muted); color: var(--text-faint); font: 0.56rem 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  @media (min-width: 700px) { .page-header { padding-top: 4rem; padding-bottom: 5rem; } .timeline-row { grid-template-columns: 150px minmax(0, 680px); gap: 2rem; padding: 1.5rem 0 2rem; } }
</style>
